  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package is a synthetic adversarial sample targeting the Greenwell sufficiency flaw: the decision rationale treats the presence of a relative-hemolysis-index alarm threshold (RH < 1) as a sufficient safety condition, while other necessary safety conditions remain not-assessed.",
